<HTML><HEAD> <link rel="stylesheet" href="../resource.css"><Title>Jacques Maritain Center: GC 2.26a</title></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#EEEEEE">
 ALT=""><A HREF="gc.htm"> Of God and His Creatures</a><hr><p>

Any quantitative infinite, -- allowing its possibility, -- still is 
infinite only in a certain category. But God transcends all the 
categories. An infinite number would not be intelligent, or just, or 
beautiful. Therefore it would fall infinitely short of God. 

